1371→     *   <li>Kafka Streams 4.x requires brokers on version 2.1 or higher. Connection attempts to
1372→     *       older brokers will fail due to unsupported protocol versions.</li>
1373→     *   <li>When {@link StreamsConfig#PROCESSING_GUARANTEE_CONFIG processing.guarantee} is set to
1374→     *       {@link StreamsConfig#EXACTLY_ONCE_V2 exactly_once_v2}, brokers must be version 2.5 or higher.
1375→     *       If the broker version is too old, the application will detect this during the first rebalance
1376→     *       and transition to {@link State#ERROR ERROR} state.</li>
1377→     * </ul>
1378→     * <p>
1379→     * Broker compatibility issues are typically detected asynchronously after {@code start()} returns.
1380→     * Use {@link #setStateListener(StateListener)} or
1381→     * {@link #setUncaughtExceptionHandler(StreamsUncaughtExceptionHandler)} to be notified of such failures.
